I'll calculate these financial ratios one by one using the given financial statements.

## Current Ratio
Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities
Current Ratio = 9,717,259.46 / 1,493,246.99 = 6.51

## Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = (2,329,939.23 / 5,064,939.23) × 100% = 46.00%

## Debt to Asset Ratio
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets
Debt to Asset Ratio = 1,493,246.99 / 15,200,446.16 = 0.10

## Net Profit Margin
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
Net Profit Margin = (707,199.17 / 5,064,939.23) × 100% = 13.96%

## Cash to Current Debt Ratio
Cash to Current Debt Ratio = (Cash on Hand + Bank Deposits) / Total Current Liabilities
Cash to Current Debt Ratio = (4,540,900.90 + 2,866,063.83) / 1,493,246.99 = 7,406,964.73 / 1,493,246.99 = 4.96

## Free Cash Flow (FCF)
FCF = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities - Capital Expenditures
FCF = -64,099.10 - 528,936.17 = -593,035.27

## Return on Assets (ROA)
ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%
ROA = (707,199.17 / 15,200,446.16) × 100% = 4.65%
